phrases: I was just about to get up...
We will meet to bargain with them early next week, all right?
My maternal grandfather died last night.
Seems he would lost touch with all of the relatives...
I come back after all this time and it is for a funeral...
I do not know about tomorrow.
It is different than a sacrifice.
I do not think it is like some penalty game.
I do not get it at all.
I am a little bit unsatisfied, but your presence
right now is more than just important.
There is no such thing in this world
Crying is not painful, it is love's sweet drops, sweet drops!
I want to keep dreaming forever, ya know?
I want to be more kind, ya know?
As long as I Am with you, I Am happy.
Girls sure are strong, ya know?
But sometimes we are weak, ya know?
Our wish is to be happy, happy, happy!
And those days will be happy, too!
Just want to make you happy!
Oh, Daikichi, you got here fast.
Just put your bags in Grandpa's room.
By the way, there was a girl in the yard.
I cannot remember, is Haruko's girl that age?
I do not know what to do from here on out...
Well, he was 79 and died a peaceful death, did not he?
Apparently, that girl is Grandpa's illegitimate child...
Grandpa did not say a thing about it...
And his lover took off, too...
It is so embarrassing, not to mention shameful...
How can you make light of this?!
Old enough not to make such thoughtless remarks!
You died at peace, huh, Grandpa?
About how much should I put in?
I know, but there is a certain standard amount, is not there?
Although these days, it is very common for sutras to be recited
and a posthumous Buddhist name to be given...
That is a large sum of money.
It is been a long time.
You always say you are busy!
Too busy to visit your own mother...
He did not even come home for New Year's.
Now be a good girl and do not run around!
You look a lot like your grandfather when he was younger...
I wonder if it is true.
I am sure my elder brother was lonely living alone, but...
Apparently, there is a maternity health record book.
It says her name is Rin.
Nevertheless, we are talking about a 79-year-old man...
of what your father would or would not have done,
I think you have got to give him his props...
Daikichi, would you bring the cushions out of the closet for me?
You are very good at cat's cradle, Reina-chan!
Next, try to make a four-square ladder!
I will take my turn watching the incense.
Hey, do not sleep in here!
Let us get some rest over there.
Daikichi says he will watch over it...
Take care of my big brother...
You get some sleep over there, too.
It is time to say goodbye to Grandpa.
I am making a field of flowers!
You, too, come over here and say goodbye.
That flower makes Grandpa the happiest.
He is not going to wake up again?
He is not going to wake up.
You really are Grandpa's child, are not you?
Where did this Yoshii Masako go?
I do not think any good would come of finding the person
who abandoned her child and ran away.
My big brother too was stubborn about it...
And she still has all of her baby teeth!
And she is not a headache!
That is why it is so boring being with her!
You can have all these if you go away!
You are like a candy shop owner!
Setting aside the matter of future plans,
who is going to take care of that child right now?
If she were a little more proper...
And she seems to be suffering from delayed speech, too...
Why do not you take her in for a while?
Y-You know that would be impossible!
I do not have that much free time on my hands!
Do you understand how hard it is to raise a child?!
Have not I made enough sacrifices over the years?!
I would feel sorry for the girl if she came over
and no one had time to look after her.
Was not this meeting supposed to be about who would take in Rin?
It is not like you have any intention of doing anything, do you, big brother?
Think about the situation a little more realistically.
In the first place, I am not even certain that she is Grandpa's child.
You have not thought it through so you cannot even give me a comeback.
For now, I say we try placing her in a facility as quickly as possible...
Want To come home with me?
Do not call me old man!
After all, you are my aunt!
It is the same road I am used to traveling
But I can see it sparkling so bright
With the sun shining down its warmth
And you here by my side...
I am already high, high, high
I am already high, high, high
All we have left is rice.
I will make a rice ball...
I do not have anything to put in the rice ball.
But it will have a tender taste.
